reviews.text:
Went here on a Friday night. Absolutely loved the atmosphere, it was packed but there are a lot of attentive and friendly staff.

The place has a real buzz and the menu is decent. We shared a starter of carpaccio beef, then had two mains, a pasta dish and the tiger king prawns.

Despite the queue of people waiting to get in we never felt rushed.

Would highly recommend.

We came here twice: once, the service was terrible but food was good, once the service was excellent but food was disappointing. Elias was wonderful - very attentive, kind and efficient. You can sit outside nicely in the heart of Munich. The interior design is very tasteful.
The ambiance was truly delightful, and the food was exceptional. Our waiter was incredibly knowledgeable and helpful, making the dining experience even more enjoyable.

Best service I have received in my 14 days in Europe. Food is delicious, pleasantly surprised by the grilled Octopus!

Hot chocolate was very rich üëçüèª
Coffee was great.

Once again, the service rendered was sincere, polite, customer-centric. The owner must be proud to have a team that is self-motivated. Good jobs guys!

P/S: wished I tried the apple pie! Saw it too late, they have a very nice display of delicious looking desserts üíú

The food was extraordinary and the service was exceptional. I visited the restaurant twice during my 4 day stay in Munich. The steak was amazing, the pasta was as good as or even better than what I would get in Italy. The dessert and coffee were good. The whole experience was exceptional.
